I loved this soup the first time I made it (though I used quite a bit less broth), but my mum didn't like it much. So when I warmed it up the next day I started with a light roux to thicken it and served it with sour cream and she loved it. Great flavor, highly recommended.

Rating: 3
I had a huge head of napa cabbage from my CSA that I was searching to put to good use in an autumn-inspired dish-- and this recipe definitely did the trick. I made a few alterations: added potatoes and a diced delicata squash to the cabbage to add body/ creaminess (without dairy) and ended up blending the entire soup with my immersion stick blender. i added shallots to the apples, carmelized and topped the creamed soup with this delicious mixture--it added a nice contrast in textures, and the sweet, tartness of the apples play nicely against the cabbage base. I also, topped mine with a little homemade pesto-- it added a brightness. My fiance (usually prefers meaty dishes) and I both really enjoyed this hearty and satisfying soup on a damp, New England November day!

