Rating: 4
Four forks with alterations. We had a small French cabbage, maybe 4-5 cups' worth, and two large shallots. I threw in some (cooked) slices of pork sausage while sauté-ing the cabbage, then deglazed the pan with a splash of muscadet and fished out the sausage to accompany the apples. I used dried herbes de Provence, black pepper, and vegetable bullion cubes with 3-4 cups of water; I blended the soup with a stick blender, added a splash of whole milk, and tipped in the apple/sausage combo. Yum.

